[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mika: Sunderland sign Boavista goalkeeper on two-year deal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Sunderland have signed Boavista goalkeeper Mika on a two-year deal for an undisclosed fee.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 25-year-old could make his Premier League debut against Everton on Monday.
Fifa have ratified the signing after a technical issue meant Boavista were unable to complete their requirements by the 23:00 BST deadline on 31 August.
Sunderland needed cover in goal after first choice Vito Mannone, 28, was ruled out for up to three months with an elbow injury.
